Dear Sera

I feared that might be the case. One further thing occurs to me. You say 
you want to analyse means which implies each primary study gives rise to 
one mean only. That is an unusual sort of study, it would be more usual 
to have two or more groups and a comparative design. If that had been 
the case there might be a way forward of course.

Michael

